BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 2: Our Solar System) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (That night, Maya dreamed she was floating in space. She could see all the planets!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Welcome to our Solar System!' said a friendly voice. It was the Sun itself!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('I have eight planets orbiting around me,' the Sun beamed proudly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Let me introduce you to each one - they are all so different and special!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Maya zoomed past each planet, amazed by their colors and sizes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Some were rocky and small; others were giant balls of swirling gas.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (MEET THE PLANETS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 544 Td (Mercury - Closest to Sun, smallest planet, scorching hot days, freezing nights.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 528 Td (Venus - Hottest planet \(462C\), thick toxic clouds, spins backward!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 512 Td (Earth - Our home! Perfect temperature for liquid water and life.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 496 Td (Mars - The Red Planet, has the tallest volcano \(Olympus Mons, 72,000 ft\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 480 Td (Jupiter - Biggest planet, could fit 1,300 Earths inside, has 95 moons!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 464 Td (Saturn - Famous for beautiful rings made of ice and rock particles.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 448 Td (Uranus - Tilted on its side, rolls around the Sun like a ball.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 72 432 Td (Neptune - Farthest planet, windiest place in solar system \(1,200 mph winds\).) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 347 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 406 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 386 Td (* A trick to remember planet order: My Very Excited Mother Just Served Us Nachos.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 368 Td (* Jupiter is so massive its gravity protects Earth from many asteroids.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 350 Td (* One day on Venus is longer than one year on Venus \(it spins very slowly\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 317 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 301 Td (Make a scale model: if Sun is a basketball, Earth would be a tiny bead 78 feet away!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 281 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 265 Td (Why do you think Earth is the only planet with liquid water on its surface?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
