BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 3: The Moon Mission) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (In her dream, Maya put on a spacesuit and climbed into a rocket ship.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Destination: The Moon!' announced the computer. Maya held on tight!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The engines roared and Maya felt herself pressed back into her seat.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (After three days of travel, the Moon appeared in her window - huge and gray.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (She bounced across the surface in the low gravity, jumping incredibly high!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('I weigh only 15 pounds here!' Maya laughed, doing somersaults in the dust.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE OF OUR MOON) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (The Moon's gravity is only 1/6 of Earth's - you could jump 6 times higher!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (There is no air on the Moon, so astronauts must wear spacesuits with oxygen.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The Moon has phases because we see different amounts of its sunlit side.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (New Moon, Crescent, Quarter, Gibbous, Full Moon - the cycle takes 29.5 days.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (The Moon is slowly moving away from Earth - about 1.5 inches per year!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Footprints on the Moon will last millions of years because there is no wind or rain.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 379 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 438 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 418 Td (* 12 people have walked on the Moon, all between 1969 and 1972.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 400 Td (* The Moon causes ocean tides on Earth through its gravitational pull.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 382 Td (* A Moon 'day' lasts about 14 Earth days, followed by 14 days of night.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 349 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 333 Td (Use a flashlight and a ball in a dark room to recreate Moon phases!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 313 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 297 Td (If you weigh 60 lbs on Earth, how much would you weigh on the Moon?) Tj ET

endstream
