BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 5: The Red Planet) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Maya's comet ride brought her close to a rusty-red world: Mars!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She landed gently on the dusty red surface and looked around in awe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The sky was a pinkish color, and the landscape was covered in red rocks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('It looks like a desert!' Maya said. 'But much colder and with barely any air.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (In the distance, she could see an enormous volcano rising above the horizon.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('That must be Olympus Mons - the biggest volcano in the entire solar system!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE OF MARS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Mars has a very thin atmosphere - mostly carbon dioxide, not breathable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The red color comes from iron oxide \(rust\) in the soil and dust.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Olympus Mons is 72,000 feet tall - nearly 3 times taller than Mt. Everest!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Mars has seasons, polar ice caps, and the longest canyon \(Valles Marineris\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (A day on Mars is 24 hours 37 minutes - almost the same as Earth!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Scientists have found evidence that liquid water once flowed on Mars's surface.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 379 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 438 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 418 Td (* Mars has two tiny moons: Phobos and Deimos \(Fear and Panic in Greek\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 400 Td (* NASA's rovers \(Curiosity, Perseverance\) are exploring Mars right now!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 382 Td (* A trip to Mars would take about 7-9 months with current technology.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 349 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 333 Td (Mix red paint with sand to make 'Mars soil.' Compare it to real Earth soil!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 313 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 297 Td (What would humans need to survive living on Mars? Make a list!) Tj ET

endstream
