BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 181.2 720 Td (Chapter 6: The Giant Storm) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Maya blasted off from Mars and headed toward the biggest planet of all.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Jupiter grew larger and larger in her window until it filled the entire view.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('It is ENORMOUS!' Maya exclaimed. This planet could swallow Earth 1,300 times!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Colorful bands of clouds swirled across its surface in beautiful patterns.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Then she spotted it: a massive red oval bigger than Earth itself.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('The Great Red Spot!' Maya whispered. 'A storm that has raged for over 400 years!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE OF JUPITER) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Jupiter is a gas giant - it has no solid surface to stand on!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The Great Red Spot is a hurricane-like storm raging for at least 400 years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (This storm is so big that TWO Earths could fit inside it!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Jupiter spins incredibly fast - one day is only about 10 hours long.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (It has at least 95 known moons, including four giant ones discovered by Galileo.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Jupiter's gravity is so strong it acts like a cosmic vacuum cleaner for asteroids.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 379 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 438 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 418 Td (* Jupiter's moon Europa may have an ocean under its icy surface - possible life!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 400 Td (* Jupiter is made mostly of hydrogen and helium, like a star that never ignited.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 382 Td (* The planet has faint rings too, but they are very thin and hard to see.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 349 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 333 Td (Swirl food coloring in water to see how Jupiter's bands and storms look!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 313 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 297 Td (Why can't you land on Jupiter? What would happen if you tried?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
