BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 7: Saturn's Rings) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Beyond Jupiter, Maya saw the most beautiful sight of her entire journey.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Saturn floated like a golden jewel, surrounded by spectacular glowing rings!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('They look solid from far away,' Maya noticed as she flew closer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (But up close, she could see billions of individual pieces of ice and rock.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Some chunks were tiny as grains of sand; others were as big as houses!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Maya carefully weaved between the ring particles, feeling like she was in a snowstorm.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE OF SATURN'S RINGS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Saturn's rings are made of billions of pieces of ice and rock.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The pieces range from tiny grains to chunks as big as a house.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The rings are incredibly wide \(282,000 km\) but very thin \(only 10-30 meters!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Saturn is the least dense planet - it would float in a bathtub of water!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Like Jupiter, Saturn is a gas giant with no solid ground.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Saturn has 146 known moons - more than any other planet!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 379 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 438 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 418 Td (* Saturn's moon Titan has lakes and rivers - but they are liquid methane, not water!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 400 Td (* You could fit 764 Earths inside Saturn.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 382 Td (* Saturn's rings may disappear in about 100 million years as they slowly fall inward.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 349 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 333 Td (Spin a coin on a table - see how it looks like a ring? That is how Saturn's rings appear!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 313 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 297 Td (If Saturn could float in water, what does that tell you about its density?) Tj ET

endstream
