BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 200.4 720 Td (Chapter 8: Coming Home) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (As Maya flew past Neptune and the edge of our solar system, she turned back.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (From out here, Earth was just a tiny pale blue dot in the vast darkness.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Our whole world... everything and everyone I love... is on that tiny dot.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Maya felt a warm hand on her shoulder. 'Time to wake up,' said Grandpa.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (She opened her eyes. She was back on the porch, stars still twinkling above.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Grandpa, I had the most amazing dream! I visited every planet!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 564 Td (Grandpa smiled. 'The universe is full of wonders waiting to be discovered.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 548 Td ('Anyone can explore space - all you need is curiosity and determination.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 532 Td ('Scientists, astronauts, engineers - they all started as kids who looked up and wondered.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 516 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 500 Td (MORAL: Dream big - the universe is waiting for curious minds like yours!) Tj ET
